            <term xml:id="term-k000291-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">顺身串</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000291-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">顺身串</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000291-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">shùnshēnchuàn</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000291-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">shun-shen-ch`uan</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000291-6" xml:lang="en" source="#biblk000291-1" >longitudinal tie</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000291</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Shunshenchuan 順身串, a type of <term ref="/keyword/k000289">chuan</term> 串 in traditional Chinese architecture, is a connecting component inserted between columns and positioned parallel to the direction 
                  of the ridge purlin. Its sectional dimension is typically as high and wide as one cai 材 (a timber of standard width and height in Song-dynasty carpentry), measuring 15 fen 分 in 
                  height and 10 fen in width. The term shunshenchuan first appeared in the Yingzao fashi (Li, 2009, 19.2b).</p> 
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">順身串是串的一種，作為建築構件名稱最早出現在宋《營造法式》（李誡2009，19.2b）。順身串是順屋身方向的柱間聯繫構件。《營造法式》規定其斷面廣厚如材（15分x10分）。實例如福州華林寺大殿（964年）。</p>                  
            </note>
